{"id":"binary-to-hex","slug":"binary-to-hex","name":"Binary to Hexadecimal Converter","category":"converters","icon":"💻","description":"Convert binary numbers to hexadecimal. Group binary digits in sets of 4 to get each hex digit.","tags":["binary","hex","hexadecimal","number system","converter"],"fields":[{"id":"bits","label":"Binary Length (bits)","type":"number","defaultValue":8,"constraint":{"min":4,"max":32,"step":4}},{"id":"hexDigits","label":"Hex digits needed","type":"computed","precision":0,"helpText":"bits / 4"},{"id":"maxDecimal","label":"Max decimal value","type":"computed","precision":0},{"id":"maxHexFF","label":"Is 8-bit (FF max)?","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Binary Word Size","fields":["bits"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Hex Info","fields":["hexDigits","maxDecimal"]}],"formulas":{"hexDigits":"bits / 4","maxDecimal":"2^bits - 1","maxHexFF":"bits/4"},"explanation":"## Binary to Hex Conversion\n\nGroup 4 bits → 1 hex digit:\n\n| Binary | Hex |\n|--------|-----|\n| 0000 | 0 |\n| 0001 | 1 |\n| 1010 | A |\n| 1111 | F |\n\n**Example:** 10101111 → 1010=A, 1111=F → **AF**","examples":[{"label":"8-bit (1 byte)","inputs":{"bits":8}},{"label":"16-bit (2 bytes)","inputs":{"bits":16}}]}
